                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, regular hand; broadly spaced letters</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg><date>Second half of the 18th century - first half of the
                           19th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the protagonist; two lines
                           (alternating with a black line) on the incipit page of Texts I-II;
                           selected lines in Text I; incipit of each miracle in Text II; elements of
                           the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 The second
                           component of the names of the donors (fol. 39rb) and two lines on fol.
                           117ra-rb are rubricated in vivid vermilion, in a secondary hand.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The name of the scribe, Tǝsbǝʾta Qāl, who
                        wrote Additiones 2-3 and inserted the names of the donors, is mentioned in
                        the concluding supplication formula of Text I, <locus target="#96vb">96vb</locus>.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2va">ff. 2va-6rb</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Taʾammǝra Giyorgis, “Miracles of George”: 3 miracles. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <note>The text is written in the main hand. Nomina
                           sacra, name of the protagonist or the word qǝddus “saint”, two lines of
                           the incipit and incipit of the miracles are rubricated. The ruling of
                           fols. 1 and 6 is the same as that of Texts I-II. On <locus from="2r" to="5v">2r-5v</locus> there are 30 lines. The name Gabra Ḥǝywat is
                           written at the end of the text on <locus target="#6rb">6rb</locus>
                           , in the same hand as Additiones 2-3. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#97ra">ff. 97ra</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">: Donation note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#97ra">97ra-b</locus>ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ ዘተሳየጦ፡
                              በንዋዩ፡ ወርቈ። ዘወሀቦሙ፡ ለ፲፪፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ዘሰረቃ… [<locus target="#97rb">97rb</locus>] ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘቤተ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ወዘአቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ አቡነ፡ ገበረ፡ መድኅን፡
                              ወብእሲቱ፡ አመተ፡ ስላሴ፡ ከመትኵኖሙ፡ መርህ…</quote>
                           <note> The note is crudely written by the secondary hand
                           of Tǝsbǝʾtä Qāl (s. also Additiones 3 and 4). It states that the Ms. was
                           purchased by ʾabuna Gabra Ḥǝywat and donated to the Bet Ḥawāryāt church.
                           Subsequently, it mentions ʾabuna Gabra Ḥǝywat, his wife Walatta Śǝllāse
                           and ʾabuna Gabra Madḫǝn. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#97rb">ff. 97rb</locus>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote">: Ownership note. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <note> The note is crudely written by the secondary hand
                           of Tǝsbǝʾta Qāl (s. also Additiones 2 and 4). It states that the Ms.
                           belongs to the the Bet Ḥawāryāt church as well as to ʾabuna Gabra Ḥǝywat,
                              ʾabuna Gabra Madḫǝn and his wife Walatta Śǝllāse. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#117r">f. 117r</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">: Donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           
                           <note> The note is crudely written, by the secondary hand of Tǝsbǝʾta Qāl
                              (s. also Additiones 2 and 3), over an almost completely erased text
                              (probably the original donation note). It states that the Ms. was
                              donated to the Bet Ḥawāryāt church by Gabra Ḥǝywat and Walatta
                              Śǝllāse. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#117r">f. 117r</locus>
                           <desc type="MagicText">: Magical recipe.</desc>
                           
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <note> The note is carefully written in the main hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letters or words are written interlineally, in a
                           secondary hand: <locus target="#7vb">7vb</locus>, 8va, 9rb, 10rab.
 -
                           Minor notes, writing exercises, doodles: e.g., <locus target="#1rv">1rv</locus>, 2rv, 6v, 7r, 14r, 17r, 28r, 33r, 41r, 76v, 77r, 86v,
                           97v, 98r, 107v, 108r, 116va, 117v.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days of the week written in the upper margin of some fols., in a
                              secondary hand: በእለተ፡ ሠሉስ: <locus target="#27va">fol. 27va</locus>
                              በእለተ፡ ረቡዕ: <locus target="#39ra">fol. 39ra</locus> በእለተ፡ ሐሙስ: <locus target="#61va">fol. 61va</locus> በእለተ፡ ዓርብ: <locus target="#76rb">fol. 76rb</locus> በእለተ፡ ቀዳሚት: <locus target="#86vb">fol.
                                 86vb</locus> በእለተ፡ ዕሑድ: <locus target="#93rb">fol.
                              93rb</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards covered with dark brown tooled
                           leather.
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">Small holes are visible on the spine fold
                           of the quires, one close to the head and one close to the tail of the
                           codex.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">Blind tooled ornament on the dark brown leather cover
                           (at least 7 tools were used: fourfold line fillet, triple line fillet,
                           double circle, interlaced line fillet, criss-cross, wave form, cross
                           hatching).</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
